).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C3735DEAFFADFFB41DEFF8F41F81F809" pageId="16" pageNumber="45" type="distribution">
<paragraph id="8BD60E61FFADFFB41DEFF8F41E8BF8C3" blockId="16.[151,1437,151,1979]" pageId="16" pageNumber="45">
<emphasis id="B91DD273FFADFFB41DEFF8F41C17F8A1" bold="true" box="[201,354,1815,1840]" pageId="16" pageNumber="45">Distribution.</emphasis>
From 
<collectingCountry id="F37E4EF1FFADFFB41C89F8FB1C8BF8A1" box="[431,510,1816,1840]" name="Greece" pageId="16" pageNumber="45">Greece</collectingCountry>
eastwards to eastern 
<collectingCountry id="F37E4EF1FFADFFB41FD2F8FB1E31F8A1" box="[756,836,1816,1840]" name="Turkey" pageId="16" pageNumber="45">Turkey</collectingCountry>
and southwards to 
<collectingCountry id="F37E4EF1FFADFFB41904F8FB1905F8A1" box="[1058,1136,1816,1840]" name="Jordan" pageId="16" pageNumber="45">Jordan</collectingCountry>
. 
<taxonomicName id="4C6975E2FFADFFB4195AF8FA1874F8A1" box="[1148,1281,1817,1840]" class="Insecta" family="Megachilidae" genus="Hoplitis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="16" pageNumber="45" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="serainae">
<emphasis id="B91DD273FFADFFB4195AF8FA1874F8A1" box="[1148,1281,1817,1840]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="45">H. serainae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was found to occur syntopically with 
<taxonomicName id="4C6975E2FFADFFB41C82F8DF1F54F8C2" box="[420,545,1851,1875]" class="Insecta" family="Megachilidae" genus="Hoplitis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="16" pageNumber="45" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="nicolaei">
<emphasis id="B91DD273FFADFFB41C82F8DF1F54F8C2" box="[420,545,1851,1875]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="45">H. nicolaei</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
at several localities in 
<collectingCountry id="F37E4EF1FFADFFB41E04F8D91E04F8C3" box="[802,881,1850,1874]" name="Greece" pageId="16" pageNumber="45">Greece</collectingCountry>
and 
<collectingCountry id="F37E4EF1FFADFFB41E8EF8D91E8FF8C3" box="[936,1018,1850,1874]" name="Turkey" pageId="16" pageNumber="45">Turkey</collectingCountry>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BD60E61FFADFFB41DEFF8BE1F81F809" blockId="16.[151,1437,151,1979]" pageId="16" pageNumber="45">
<emphasis id="B91DD273FFADFFB41DEFF8BE1C2CF8E4" bold="true" box="[201,345,1885,1909]" pageId="16" pageNumber="45">Host plants.</emphasis>
Two pollen samples from the same locality, where only males of 
<taxonomicName id="4C6975E2FFADFFB41919F8BD19B6F8E4" box="[1087,1219,1886,1909]" class="Insecta" family="Megachilidae" genus="Hoplitis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="16" pageNumber="45" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="serainae">
<emphasis id="B91DD273FFADFFB41919F8BD19B6F8E4" box="[1087,1219,1886,1909]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="45">H. serainae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
but no males of 
<taxonomicName id="4C6975E2FFADFFB418A7F8BD1D84F809" class="Insecta" family="Megachilidae" genus="Hoplitis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="16" pageNumber="45" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="nicolaei">
<emphasis id="B91DD273FFADFFB418A7F8BD1D84F809" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="45">H. nicolaei</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
were collected, consist of pollen of 
<taxonomicName id="4C6975E2FFADFFB41FA1F8631F85F809" box="[647,752,1920,1944]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Linaceae" kingdom="Plantae" order="Malpighiales" pageId="16" pageNumber="45" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="family">Linaceae</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C3735DEAFFADFFB41DEFF8401E3BF82B" box="[201,846,1954,1979]" pageId="16" pageNumber="45" type="etymology">
<paragraph id="8BD60E61FFADFFB41DEFF8401E3BF82B" blockId="16.[151,1437,151,1979]" box="[201,846,1954,1979]" pageId="16" pageNumber="45">
<emphasis id="B91DD273FFADFFB41DEFF8401C25F82A" bold="true" box="[201,336,1955,1979]" pageId="16" pageNumber="45">Etymology.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="4C6975E2FFADFFB41C70F8411CC7F82B" box="[342,434,1954,1978]" class="Insecta" family="Megachilidae" genus="Hoplitis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="16" pageNumber="45" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="serainae">serainae</taxonomicName>
= dedicated to my daugther Seraina.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
